1
00:00:06,600 --> 00:00:09,520
[Fall of 1994]
Yunhui Pharma

2
00:00:09,840 --> 00:00:12,960
is Halan's leading enterprise
with solid partnerships

3
00:00:13,360 --> 00:00:14,960
with over 100 pharmaceutical companies

4
00:00:14,960 --> 00:00:17,640
and raw material suppliers nationwide.

5
00:00:48,240 --> 00:00:49,120
Wait, Ms. Jiang.

6
00:00:49,460 --> 00:00:51,140
[Halan Yunhui Pharma]

7
00:00:53,360 --> 00:00:54,160
This is for you.

8
00:00:55,340 --> 00:00:56,700
[Adhesive Bandage]

9
00:01:02,600 --> 00:01:03,400
Thank you.

10
00:01:15,080 --> 00:01:15,880
Mr. Wang,

11
00:01:17,680 --> 00:01:18,720
how can I help you?

12
00:01:19,800 --> 00:01:22,240
I've been feeling a bit unwell lately.

13
00:01:22,440 --> 00:01:23,480
I keep coughing,

14
00:01:24,320 --> 00:01:25,320
so I came to buy some medicine.

15
00:01:27,440 --> 00:01:28,280
Do you have a fever?

16
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:31,200
Not really.

17
00:01:35,440 --> 00:01:36,120
Then

18
00:01:37,120 --> 00:01:38,640
take these three kinds of medicine.

19
00:01:46,160 --> 00:01:46,840
Mr. Wang,

20
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:48,800
if you keep feeling unwell,

21
00:01:49,360 --> 00:01:51,280
you should go see a doctor.

22
00:01:55,480 --> 00:01:58,520
I'm usually quite healthy.

23
00:02:10,820 --> 00:02:14,820
[Producer Zhang Yimou]

24
00:03:39,140 --> 00:03:44,700
[The First Shot]

25
00:03:44,780 --> 00:03:47,620
[Episode 19]

26
00:04:24,830 --> 00:04:25,550
Bei!

27
00:04:30,390 --> 00:04:31,750
Wow, look at you showing off.

28
00:04:31,910 --> 00:04:32,710
Why are you here, Bei?

29
00:04:32,710 --> 00:04:33,510
You should've told me you were coming.

30
00:04:33,950 --> 00:04:35,750
I'm here to see
if you're taking work seriously.

31
00:04:36,470 --> 00:04:37,710
Good thing I wasn't slacking off.

32
00:04:37,990 --> 00:04:39,470
Didn't you say you had a fever?

33
00:04:39,470 --> 00:04:40,550
Are you better already?

34
00:04:40,790 --> 00:04:41,590
I'm still having a fever.

35
00:04:44,270 --> 00:04:45,630
No way this is a fever.

36
00:04:45,630 --> 00:04:46,910
You're just sweating
from roller-skating.

37
00:04:48,030 --> 00:04:48,910
Maybe.

38
00:04:51,510 --> 00:04:53,110
If you're sick,

39
00:04:53,790 --> 00:04:55,070
take some time off.

40
00:04:55,270 --> 00:04:56,790
Don't push yourself too hard.

41
00:04:57,070 --> 00:04:59,310
But I've never seen you take a sick day.

42
00:04:59,310 --> 00:05:00,750
Why are you arguing with me?

43
00:05:01,270 --> 00:05:03,310
I'm not.
I just can't afford to take leave.

44
00:05:03,510 --> 00:05:05,150
Every day I miss
is a day I don't get paid,

45
00:05:05,190 --> 00:05:06,630
and they'll dock my bonus too.

46
00:05:06,790 --> 00:05:07,590
Besides, I promised Mao

47
00:05:07,590 --> 00:05:08,830
I'd buy her a birthday present.

48
00:05:10,830 --> 00:05:12,190
Your shift is almost over, right?

49
00:05:12,510 --> 00:05:13,310
Yeah.

50
00:05:13,750 --> 00:05:14,550
Come with me after work.

51
00:05:14,550 --> 00:05:15,630
Let's go sweat it out.

52
00:05:16,030 --> 00:05:17,430
Don't bother, Bei.

53
00:05:17,430 --> 00:05:18,190
Hurry up.

54
00:05:18,190 --> 00:05:18,990
Get changed, and let's go.

55
00:05:20,030 --> 00:05:20,790
Come on.

56
00:05:21,150 --> 00:05:21,950
Hurry up!

57
00:05:22,070 --> 00:05:23,110
Alright, give me a moment.

58
00:05:55,270 --> 00:05:56,270
Come down and soak for a bit.

59
00:05:56,910 --> 00:05:58,790
Bei, maybe I should just take a shower.

60
00:05:58,790 --> 00:06:00,070
I'm really not used to soaking.

61
00:06:00,270 --> 00:06:01,470
Just get down here and soak for a while.

62
00:06:01,550 --> 00:06:02,630
Here, you got to soak in a bath.

63
00:06:02,630 --> 00:06:03,350
Come on.

64
00:06:04,710 --> 00:06:06,030
Get down here and soak. Hurry up.

65
00:06:07,910 --> 00:06:09,070
How can you live in the Northeast

66
00:06:09,070 --> 00:06:10,390
without soaking in the bath?

67
00:06:12,270 --> 00:06:13,070
Sit here.

68
00:06:19,150 --> 00:06:20,710
How do you feel? Isn't it good?

69
00:06:23,470 --> 00:06:25,030
Why are you still wrapped in that towel?

70
00:06:26,030 --> 00:06:27,110
I'm not used to this.

71
00:06:27,830 --> 00:06:28,630
Take it off.

72
00:06:28,630 --> 00:06:30,510
No one soaks in a bath with a towel on.

73
00:06:30,510 --> 00:06:31,750
People will think you're crazy.

74
00:06:31,830 --> 00:06:32,750
Come on. Take it off.

75
00:06:33,430 --> 00:06:34,350
Take it off.

76
00:06:35,590 --> 00:06:36,550
Enjoy the soak.

77
00:06:38,150 --> 00:06:39,790
I pulled out my gun and fired a shot.

78
00:06:40,470 --> 00:06:41,270
I hit him.

79
00:06:41,590 --> 00:06:43,150
His left shoulder twitched.

80
00:06:43,430 --> 00:06:44,270
So I'm sure of it.

81
00:06:46,030 --> 00:06:46,830
What's wrong?

82
00:06:47,390 --> 00:06:48,190
Nothing.

83
00:06:49,790 --> 00:06:51,030
Then don't stare at me like that.

84
00:06:51,030 --> 00:06:52,030
It makes me uncomfortable.

85
00:06:52,350 --> 00:06:53,350
What? Can't I even look at you?

86
00:06:53,350 --> 00:06:54,270
What's the big deal?

87
00:06:58,550 --> 00:06:59,350
This is nice.

88
00:07:00,350 --> 00:07:01,150
It feels good, right?

89
00:07:02,870 --> 00:07:04,070
Have you never soaked in a bath before?

90
00:07:05,550 --> 00:07:06,550
I'm not used to it.

91
00:07:07,510 --> 00:07:08,630
Why?

92
00:07:08,630 --> 00:07:09,550
There are all men here.

93
00:07:09,990 --> 00:07:11,350
Soaking helps you relax.

94
00:07:12,470 --> 00:07:13,950
Just take off that towel.

95
00:07:14,030 --> 00:07:15,510
Stop covering yourself up.

96
00:07:15,510 --> 00:07:17,470
Soaking with a towel on?

97
00:07:17,470 --> 00:07:18,350
What were you thinking?

98
00:07:19,630 --> 00:07:20,430
It feels good, right?

99
00:07:23,710 --> 00:07:24,630
What's that?

100
00:07:26,470 --> 00:07:27,230
It's nothing.

101
00:07:27,230 --> 00:07:28,070
Just a scrape

102
00:07:28,310 --> 00:07:29,310
from being a rowdy kid.

103
00:07:29,390 --> 00:07:30,230
That's a big scar.

104
00:07:30,790 --> 00:07:31,590
Let me take a look.

105
00:07:31,590 --> 00:07:32,350
It's nothing.

106
00:07:32,350 --> 00:07:33,590
What's the harm in showing me?

107
00:07:33,750 --> 00:07:34,550
Let me see.

108
00:07:49,470 --> 00:07:50,270
How old were you

109
00:07:53,190 --> 00:07:54,310
when you got this scar?

110
00:07:58,830 --> 00:07:59,870
Eleven or twelve, I think.

111
00:08:01,310 --> 00:08:02,670
I don't really remember.

112
00:08:15,070 --> 00:08:16,590
Were... Were you ever kidnapped

113
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:22,270
by human traffickers as a kid?

114
00:09:32,190 --> 00:09:32,870
You little brat!

115
00:09:32,870 --> 00:09:34,510
You're always up to no good!

116
00:09:34,710 --> 00:09:36,030
You never behave!

117
00:09:40,950 --> 00:09:41,630
Lele.

118
00:09:42,190 --> 00:09:42,950
Lele!

119
00:09:49,190 --> 00:09:49,990
Lele,

120
00:09:50,590 --> 00:09:51,550
I'm sorry.

121
00:09:52,310 --> 00:09:53,550
Does it hurt a lot?

122
00:10:01,870 --> 00:10:02,910
It doesn't hurt.

123
00:10:04,710 --> 00:10:06,070
Not at all.

124
00:10:09,190 --> 00:10:12,870
But, Bei, I'm so cold.

125
00:10:17,230 --> 00:10:18,430
Do you feel any better now?

126
00:10:22,670 --> 00:10:23,710
It's all my fault.

127
00:10:28,230 --> 00:10:29,030
It's okay.

128
00:10:30,430 --> 00:10:31,470
I'll be fine

129
00:10:31,470 --> 00:10:32,790
by tomorrow.

130
00:10:36,190 --> 00:10:37,150
See, Bei?

131
00:10:38,470 --> 00:10:40,190
I can protect you too.

132
00:10:42,790 --> 00:10:44,230
I'm the one who should protect you.

133
00:10:46,990 --> 00:10:47,790
We're friends.

134
00:10:49,110 --> 00:10:50,750
Friends are supposed
to protect each other.

135
00:10:56,430 --> 00:10:57,510
But, Bei,

136
00:10:58,430 --> 00:10:59,590
will this

137
00:11:00,590 --> 00:11:02,110
turn into an ugly scar?

138
00:11:12,190 --> 00:11:12,990
Done.

139
00:11:16,750 --> 00:11:18,070
Doesn't it look cool?

140
00:11:22,110 --> 00:11:23,270
It's so cute!

141
00:11:23,910 --> 00:11:26,110
With this, I can be brave like you.

142
00:11:30,070 --> 00:11:31,710
But does this mean
I can't take a shower anymore?

143
00:11:32,870 --> 00:11:34,110
You silly boy,

144
00:11:34,110 --> 00:11:34,950
how can you be so silly?

145
00:11:35,190 --> 00:11:36,710
If it washes off,
I'll draw another one for you.

146
00:11:39,910 --> 00:11:40,950
When we get out of here,

147
00:11:40,950 --> 00:11:42,150
I'll give you one

148
00:11:42,150 --> 00:11:43,070
that never washes off.

149
00:11:44,030 --> 00:11:44,870
Really?

150
00:11:47,790 --> 00:11:49,110
Pinky swear!

151
00:11:49,110 --> 00:11:50,590
You can never go back on your word!

152
00:12:38,270 --> 00:12:38,870
Bei.

153
00:12:39,190 --> 00:12:39,830
Bei.

154
00:12:40,070 --> 00:12:41,190
Let's go grab a bite.

155
00:12:41,310 --> 00:12:43,310
Let's go eat. I'm starving.

156
00:13:09,870 --> 00:13:11,790
When did you recognize me?

157
00:13:16,150 --> 00:13:17,830
On the night of the murder
at the white building.

158
00:13:21,910 --> 00:13:22,910
I noticed you in the distance

159
00:13:25,870 --> 00:13:27,390
as soon as you got out of the car,

160
00:13:29,110 --> 00:13:30,390
and I recognized you right away,

161
00:13:32,350 --> 00:13:33,790
my big brother, Zheng Bei.

162
00:13:40,030 --> 00:13:40,830
Captain Zheng!

163
00:14:17,510 --> 00:14:18,590
You'd grown taller

164
00:14:21,670 --> 00:14:22,550
and stronger,

165
00:14:25,910 --> 00:14:27,190
but the look in your eyes
hadn't changed.

166
00:14:32,910 --> 00:14:34,030
That's the look.

167
00:14:35,950 --> 00:14:36,910
So open and honest.

168
00:14:37,830 --> 00:14:39,350
Why didn't you tell me

169
00:14:40,150 --> 00:14:41,590
since you recognized me?

170
00:14:42,270 --> 00:14:45,030
Because you didn't recognize me, man.

171
00:14:47,630 --> 00:14:48,430
It makes sense.

172
00:14:49,510 --> 00:14:50,310
I guess

173
00:14:52,310 --> 00:14:53,790
even if you did,

174
00:14:53,790 --> 00:14:54,510
you wouldn't have

175
00:14:55,600 --> 00:14:57,080
wanted to admit it.

176
00:14:58,360 --> 00:15:00,640
In fact, I didn't plan
on reconnecting with you.

177
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:02,520
After all, you and I are not

178
00:15:03,720 --> 00:15:04,680
in the same world anymore.

179
00:15:09,040 --> 00:15:11,000
It's not like that,

180
00:15:11,920 --> 00:15:12,720
Lele.

181
00:15:13,160 --> 00:15:14,120
Don't call me Lele.

182
00:15:14,560 --> 00:15:15,520
Lele is dead.

183
00:15:23,280 --> 00:15:24,480
I really thought you were dead.

184
00:15:24,480 --> 00:15:25,440
You're right.

185
00:15:26,840 --> 00:15:27,880
I've gone through death many times over.

186
00:15:33,880 --> 00:15:34,680
Bei,

187
00:15:38,960 --> 00:15:40,200
I do bear a grudge against you.

188
00:15:46,120 --> 00:15:47,280
That day when we had drinks together,

189
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:48,600
I actually thought about killing you

190
00:15:50,960 --> 00:15:52,280
after you fell asleep.

191
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:53,840
Don't go anywhere.

192
00:15:54,480 --> 00:15:55,280
Wait for me here.

193
00:15:55,680 --> 00:15:56,760
I'll be right back.

194
00:16:17,320 --> 00:16:19,160
Do you remember what you said?

195
00:16:24,880 --> 00:16:25,960
"Don't go anywhere.

196
00:16:27,280 --> 00:16:28,360
Wait for me to come back."

197
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:33,280
Why couldn't you people
who wanted to desert me

198
00:16:33,480 --> 00:16:34,760
just tell me the truth?

199
00:16:37,200 --> 00:16:38,960
Why did you all have to lie to me?

200
00:16:41,720 --> 00:16:43,760
Stay here and wait for me to come back.

201
00:17:36,640 --> 00:17:37,840
But I'm scared.

202
00:17:38,480 --> 00:17:39,720
Where are you going, Bei?

203
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:45,800
Remember, don't make a sound.

204
00:17:46,320 --> 00:17:47,040
Wait for me to come back.

205
00:17:47,600 --> 00:17:48,760
I'll definitely come back to get you.

206
00:17:59,240 --> 00:18:01,240
It was such a cold winter.

207
00:18:05,400 --> 00:18:07,200
When the human traffickers took me back,

208
00:18:07,200 --> 00:18:08,880
I was nearly frozen stiff.

209
00:18:11,720 --> 00:18:13,840
Just before I passed out, I thought,

210
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:19,000
"My big brother must have forgotten me."

211
00:18:19,800 --> 00:18:21,280
I wasn't going to abandon you,

212
00:18:23,440 --> 00:18:24,240
I swear.

213
00:18:25,640 --> 00:18:27,440
I wasn't going to leave you there.

214
00:18:35,880 --> 00:18:37,600
After we ran off together,

215
00:18:41,160 --> 00:18:42,400
we hid in that garbage dump.

216
00:18:44,760 --> 00:18:45,960
Then I went out to get help,

217
00:18:48,760 --> 00:18:50,800
but as soon as I did, I passed out.

218
00:18:54,120 --> 00:18:55,120
I've had a high fever

219
00:18:56,320 --> 00:18:57,120
for two days.

220
00:18:58,280 --> 00:18:59,240
I've been unconscious for two days.

221
00:19:03,560 --> 00:19:04,800
As soon as I woke up,

222
00:19:04,800 --> 00:19:07,360
I took the police back
to the garbage dump to get you,

223
00:19:09,920 --> 00:19:11,520
but you were already gone.

224
00:19:13,120 --> 00:19:15,240
I took them
to the human traffickers' hideout too,

225
00:19:17,160 --> 00:19:18,680
but they'd already fled.

226
00:19:23,400 --> 00:19:25,160
I didn't know where else
to look for you.

227
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:29,160
Six months later,

228
00:19:31,440 --> 00:19:32,600
in early June,

229
00:19:34,200 --> 00:19:36,600
the police busted the human traffickers,

230
00:19:37,760 --> 00:19:38,520
and they

231
00:19:38,520 --> 00:19:40,520
dug up the body of a little boy
in the backyard.

232
00:19:41,760 --> 00:19:43,080
Both the height

233
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:46,200
and age

234
00:19:48,280 --> 00:19:49,560
matched yours.

235
00:19:54,720 --> 00:19:55,760
So you thought that was me?

236
00:20:10,520 --> 00:20:11,720
Ever since then, I've made it a habit

237
00:20:13,080 --> 00:20:14,280
to bring sodas to that garbage dump

238
00:20:16,240 --> 00:20:17,560
every year in early June

239
00:20:20,760 --> 00:20:22,280
to remember you.

240
00:21:31,080 --> 00:21:32,360
You've been through a lot
over the years.

241
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:40,880
Now that we've reunited,

242
00:21:43,960 --> 00:21:44,760
we should

243
00:21:47,840 --> 00:21:49,040
look out for each other

244
00:21:50,240 --> 00:21:52,680
no matter what happens.

245
00:21:57,110 --> 00:21:58,350
I want to take you somewhere.

246
00:22:02,630 --> 00:22:03,550
Look at me!

247
00:22:07,910 --> 00:22:09,190
You're so bad at this.

248
00:22:10,950 --> 00:22:12,350
Do you remember this place?

249
00:22:12,950 --> 00:22:13,750
Of course, I do.

250
00:22:14,710 --> 00:22:16,150
On the day we escaped,

251
00:22:16,150 --> 00:22:18,150
we ran through the woods
and crossed this river, right?

252
00:22:20,110 --> 00:22:22,510
I remember

253
00:22:22,510 --> 00:22:26,790
that we ran on this frozen river
for what felt like forever.

254
00:22:28,070 --> 00:22:28,870
That's right.

255
00:22:30,590 --> 00:22:33,630
Back then, this river seemed so wide,

256
00:22:34,710 --> 00:22:36,150
and it seemed impossible
to reach the other side.

257
00:22:40,590 --> 00:22:42,830
You were so small

258
00:22:42,830 --> 00:22:43,510
and so short

259
00:22:43,510 --> 00:22:44,310
back then.

260
00:22:44,310 --> 00:22:46,790
You could barely run on the ice!

261
00:22:47,590 --> 00:22:48,870
Are you making fun of me now?

262
00:22:50,910 --> 00:22:52,430
Trying to pull a sneak attack, are you?

263
00:22:52,430 --> 00:22:53,790
I'll throw you into the river!

264
00:22:55,630 --> 00:22:56,630
Alright, I surrender!

265
00:23:02,510 --> 00:23:03,590
Bei, don't sigh.

266
00:23:04,630 --> 00:23:06,230
Sighing brings bad luck.

267
00:23:10,350 --> 00:23:12,230
Back then, when we were
running on the ice,

268
00:23:13,110 --> 00:23:16,510
I kept hearing the ice cracking,

269
00:23:16,910 --> 00:23:19,310
and I was really worried
we'd fall into the river.

270
00:23:20,510 --> 00:23:22,150
It wouldn't have been
so bad to die together.

271
00:23:22,830 --> 00:23:23,630
At least we wouldn't have felt alone.

272
00:23:25,430 --> 00:23:26,430
I don't think so.

273
00:23:27,590 --> 00:23:29,030
I'm not ready to die yet.

274
00:23:29,790 --> 00:23:31,390
There are still
so many things I want to do.

275
00:23:32,350 --> 00:23:33,430
Not only are we going to stay alive,

276
00:23:34,630 --> 00:23:37,070
but we're also going
to make the most of this life, Xiaohai.

277
00:23:38,230 --> 00:23:39,030
No,

278
00:23:41,510 --> 00:23:42,310
Lele.

279
00:23:59,160 --> 00:24:00,720
When I was waiting for you
at the garbage dump,

280
00:24:03,440 --> 00:24:04,400
I was so scared,

281
00:24:06,760 --> 00:24:09,440
so I started singing
to whistle in the dark.

282
00:24:13,880 --> 00:24:15,560
It was that song you taught me.

283
00:24:16,110 --> 00:24:16,910
Do you remember it?

284
00:24:25,830 --> 00:24:29,310
♪I want to sing a song♪

285
00:24:30,670 --> 00:24:33,990
♪That old song♪

286
00:24:35,110 --> 00:24:38,030
♪You'll sing it softly♪

287
00:24:39,230 --> 00:24:42,630
♪And I'll follow along♪

288
00:24:43,070 --> 00:24:46,430
♪I hope you'll remember♪

289
00:24:47,350 --> 00:24:51,630
♪Forever and ever♪

290
00:24:51,710 --> 00:25:00,630
♪The shining days we shared together♪

291
00:25:27,870 --> 00:25:29,590
What's that smell?

292
00:25:29,750 --> 00:25:31,350
Is our home turning into a shelter now?

293
00:25:32,190 --> 00:25:35,510
Your brother and Xiaohai
drank until 2 AM last night.

294
00:25:35,910 --> 00:25:37,190
Mr. Gu and Xiaoguang

295
00:25:37,190 --> 00:25:38,710
carried them back here.

296
00:25:38,990 --> 00:25:40,550
They barely had any sleep.

297
00:25:41,190 --> 00:25:42,590
Just let them sleep a bit longer.

298
00:25:42,590 --> 00:25:43,510
Come on.

299
00:25:43,510 --> 00:25:44,390
Let's go.

300
00:26:40,710 --> 00:26:41,510
"Bei,

301
00:26:42,670 --> 00:26:43,630
I have an early shift today,

302
00:26:44,670 --> 00:26:45,790
so I'm off to work.

303
00:26:48,470 --> 00:26:49,710
I'll work hard

304
00:26:50,990 --> 00:26:52,790
and become someone you can be proud of."

305
00:27:10,190 --> 00:27:11,550
When drug users take meth,

306
00:27:11,630 --> 00:27:12,990
they usually block the door cracks

307
00:27:13,750 --> 00:27:15,910
to prevent the smell from escaping
and raising suspicion.

308
00:27:25,510 --> 00:27:27,230
- Police!
- Police! Don't move!

309
00:27:28,590 --> 00:27:29,830
Hang on!

310
00:27:29,830 --> 00:27:31,030
Just a moment!

311
00:27:31,110 --> 00:27:31,950
Still taking it, huh?

312
00:27:37,110 --> 00:27:37,970
Let go!

313
00:27:38,110 --> 00:27:40,150
Give me the bottle!

314
00:27:42,950 --> 00:27:43,750
Give it back!

315
00:27:44,150 --> 00:27:44,950
Give me the other hand!

316
00:27:45,510 --> 00:27:46,310
Zhang Xueyao,

317
00:27:46,550 --> 00:27:47,630
there's a woman out here!

318
00:27:48,470 --> 00:27:49,270
Come on!

319
00:28:01,910 --> 00:28:03,150
Can you hear me?

320
00:28:04,630 --> 00:28:05,430
Give me the needle.

321
00:28:09,230 --> 00:28:10,030
Look out!

322
00:28:12,630 --> 00:28:13,430
Stop moving!

323
00:28:13,430 --> 00:28:15,830
Let go of me!

324
00:28:22,670 --> 00:28:23,310
Move!

325
00:28:24,910 --> 00:28:25,830
Stop!

326
00:28:26,350 --> 00:28:28,070
Take a good look. Is this your child?

327
00:28:28,550 --> 00:28:30,190
Answer me! Is this your child?

328
00:28:36,670 --> 00:28:37,470
I've finished the interrogation, Bei.

329
00:28:37,590 --> 00:28:38,390
Here.

330
00:28:39,310 --> 00:28:40,430
The way they distribute drugs

331
00:28:40,430 --> 00:28:41,910
is getting more and more absurd.

332
00:28:42,270 --> 00:28:43,630
The goods were bought

333
00:28:43,630 --> 00:28:45,390
from a sanitation worker
under Ermen Bridge.

334
00:28:45,510 --> 00:28:46,710
And these two from the hotel

335
00:28:46,710 --> 00:28:47,870
swore they weren't dealers.

336
00:28:48,030 --> 00:28:49,270
I don't think they were lying.

337
00:28:49,270 --> 00:28:51,510
Having seen how they wouldn't even
waste a single hit,

338
00:28:51,630 --> 00:28:53,030
I think they were telling the truth.

339
00:28:53,150 --> 00:28:53,990
Let's get the facts straight first.

340
00:28:53,990 --> 00:28:54,710
Yao,

341
00:28:54,750 --> 00:28:56,510
go talk to their neighbors

342
00:28:56,510 --> 00:28:57,790
and find out more about those two.

343
00:28:58,150 --> 00:28:58,950
Xiaoguang,

344
00:28:59,230 --> 00:29:01,750
head to the bridge
and find that sanitation worker.

345
00:29:01,790 --> 00:29:02,590
- Got it.
- Bei,

346
00:29:02,870 --> 00:29:04,430
we found the kid's other guardian.

347
00:29:04,430 --> 00:29:05,350
He'll be here to pick up this kid soon.

348
00:29:06,910 --> 00:29:07,710
The kid's father?

349
00:29:08,150 --> 00:29:08,950
Grandfather.

350
00:29:09,230 --> 00:29:10,870
No idea who the father is.

351
00:29:12,470 --> 00:29:14,150
I can't believe

352
00:29:14,350 --> 00:29:16,430
she just left such a cute baby
on the windowsill.

353
00:29:16,670 --> 00:29:18,230
Drugs really are destructive,

354
00:29:18,350 --> 00:29:19,150
aren't they?

355
00:29:21,470 --> 00:29:22,630
Meth causes

356
00:29:22,990 --> 00:29:24,670
even greater harm
than ecstasy and ketamine.

357
00:29:24,870 --> 00:29:26,270
It leads to physical dysfunction

358
00:29:26,390 --> 00:29:28,230
and destroys the nervous system.

359
00:29:28,550 --> 00:29:29,630
People under its control

360
00:29:29,630 --> 00:29:31,230
become emotionally numb,

361
00:29:31,670 --> 00:29:33,790
losing even the most basic human dignity

362
00:29:33,790 --> 00:29:34,790
and feelings.

363
00:29:39,190 --> 00:29:39,990
There, there.

364
00:29:40,510 --> 00:29:42,110
I've got you.

365
00:29:42,310 --> 00:29:43,750
Stop staring.

366
00:29:44,670 --> 00:29:45,670
Why did you have to scare the baby?

367
00:29:46,990 --> 00:29:47,710
There, there.

368
00:29:47,710 --> 00:29:48,670
Let's ignore that scary man.

369
00:29:48,670 --> 00:29:50,030
I wonder if the baby will

370
00:29:50,030 --> 00:29:51,710
remember what happened today.

371
00:29:51,750 --> 00:29:53,550
This could cause serious trauma.

372
00:29:53,550 --> 00:29:55,230
She's too young to remember this,

373
00:29:55,790 --> 00:29:56,550
right?

374
00:29:56,550 --> 00:29:57,150
Memory

375
00:29:57,150 --> 00:29:59,710
usually starts forming
between the ages of two and three,

376
00:30:00,710 --> 00:30:01,590
but awareness begins

377
00:30:01,590 --> 00:30:03,150
as early as one month old.

378
00:30:04,030 --> 00:30:06,270
Some images can sink
into the subconscious mind.

379
00:30:06,350 --> 00:30:08,190
Not remembering
doesn't mean they won't be affected.

380
00:30:08,430 --> 00:30:09,230
Alright.

381
00:30:09,350 --> 00:30:10,550
Let's trace the source

382
00:30:10,670 --> 00:30:12,150
and get to the root of the problem.

383
00:30:12,150 --> 00:30:12,710
Got it.

384
00:30:12,710 --> 00:30:13,350
Understood.

385
00:30:13,350 --> 00:30:23,170
[Halan Detention Center]

386
00:30:52,550 --> 00:30:53,350
Madam,

387
00:30:53,990 --> 00:30:54,870
I'm out.

388
00:30:55,030 --> 00:30:56,150
Good.

389
00:30:56,790 --> 00:30:58,310
But don't cause any more trouble.

390
00:30:59,270 --> 00:31:02,070
If what happened with Song back then
comes to light,

391
00:31:02,070 --> 00:31:03,270
