00:39:31,070 --> 00:39:33,350
See, as soon as that float moves,

569
00:39:33,470 --> 00:39:34,790
I can pull the line.

570
00:39:35,350 --> 00:39:36,150
Mao!

571
00:39:36,920 --> 00:39:38,200
Why did you run off again?

572
00:39:44,640 --> 00:39:45,720
It's you.

573
00:39:46,080 --> 00:39:46,880
Hello.

574
00:39:48,640 --> 00:39:49,320
What are you...?

575
00:39:49,800 --> 00:39:51,000
I'm just hanging out with my kid here.

576
00:39:51,000 --> 00:39:52,360
Mao, say hello to Uncle Jianmin.

577
00:39:52,920 --> 00:39:53,720
Hello, Uncle Jianmin.

578
00:39:54,640 --> 00:39:55,440
Hello, Mao.

579
00:39:55,920 --> 00:39:58,280
Mommy, can I watch him fish?

580
00:39:58,320 --> 00:39:59,680
Let's not bother Uncle Jianmin.

581
00:39:59,960 --> 00:40:01,400
How about we go fly the kite instead?

582
00:40:01,680 --> 00:40:02,480
Okay.

583
00:40:02,600 --> 00:40:03,760
We're leaving then.

584
00:40:04,680 --> 00:40:05,360
Let's go.

585
00:40:13,280 --> 00:40:14,080
You weren't bothering me at all.

586
00:40:39,080 --> 00:40:39,880
Thank you.

587
00:41:07,400 --> 00:41:08,440
Hey, Mao!

588
00:41:09,680 --> 00:41:11,400
I... I've caught some fish,

589
00:41:11,400 --> 00:41:12,000
but I can't eat them all by myself.

590
00:41:12,000 --> 00:41:13,440
How about I give you one?

591
00:41:13,880 --> 00:41:15,720
Mommy doesn't like fish.

592
00:41:15,760 --> 00:41:17,360
She thinks they're too bony.

593
00:41:18,560 --> 00:41:19,880
Thank you anyway.

594
00:41:20,240 --> 00:41:21,160
You should keep them.

595
00:41:21,240 --> 00:41:22,600
If you can't finish them,
you can freeze them.

596
00:41:23,800 --> 00:41:24,640
Thanks again.

597
00:41:25,120 --> 00:41:25,920
Let's go.

598
00:41:27,160 --> 00:41:28,120
Goodbye, Uncle Jianmin.

599
00:41:47,360 --> 00:41:48,920
Now that you have Jianmin
to pick out the bones for you,

600
00:41:49,720 --> 00:41:50,840
you like eating fish, don't you?

601
00:41:51,760 --> 00:41:54,440
It's like I've been
catching up on all the fish

602
00:41:54,440 --> 00:41:55,760
I missed out on as a kid.

603
00:42:01,960 --> 00:42:04,040
Take this after meals.

604
00:42:04,160 --> 00:42:06,000
Taking it on an empty stomach
will hurt your stomach.

605
00:42:10,600 --> 00:42:11,200
Bei.

606
00:42:16,440 --> 00:42:17,480
What's with this?

607
00:42:18,720 --> 00:42:20,200
I got hit by a motorcycle.

608
00:42:21,400 --> 00:42:22,880
That's not what I'm asking about.

609
00:42:25,680 --> 00:42:27,760
It's just a small injury.
It'll heal in a couple of days.

610
00:42:28,960 --> 00:42:30,800
I'm asking why your foot
is on the table!

611
00:42:30,880 --> 00:42:32,400
Bei, what's wrong with you?

612
00:42:32,520 --> 00:42:33,520
He's injured!

613
00:42:33,520 --> 00:42:34,880
So you're a hero now?

614
00:42:35,560 --> 00:42:36,560
And you're taking medicine
for this tiny injury?

615
00:42:37,000 --> 00:42:38,320
He's still injured!

616
00:42:38,680 --> 00:42:40,160
I'm talking to him.
Why do you keep jumping in?

617
00:42:40,680 --> 00:42:43,200
You're always so annoying.

618
00:42:43,200 --> 00:42:44,080
I hate talking to you!

619
00:42:44,560 --> 00:42:45,800
You think I like talking to you?

620
00:42:46,080 --> 00:42:46,960
Mom wants to talk to you.

621
00:42:48,320 --> 00:42:49,760
You're such a nuisance now.

622
00:42:49,760 --> 00:42:50,840
I liked you better when you were little.

623
00:42:51,920 --> 00:42:53,320
What? Am I wrong?

624
00:42:53,600 --> 00:42:55,200
You're getting meaner as you grow up.

625
00:42:59,880 --> 00:43:00,680
You're very likable,

626
00:43:00,680 --> 00:43:02,880
just as likable as always.

627
00:43:04,480 --> 00:43:06,680
So, are you really
not going to the concert?

628
00:43:06,920 --> 00:43:08,560
It wasn't easy to get that ticket.

629
00:43:09,230 --> 00:43:11,630
Aren't you a huge fan
of those two pop stars?

630
00:43:13,190 --> 00:43:14,470
I'm not that much of a fan now.

631
00:43:15,070 --> 00:43:17,070
You're over them just like that?

632
00:43:19,750 --> 00:43:20,670
Well,

633
00:43:22,070 --> 00:43:23,510
feelings can change

634
00:43:24,190 --> 00:43:25,870
in the blink of an eye.

635
00:43:29,070 --> 00:43:31,750
Do you know what I mean?

636
00:43:38,030 --> 00:43:41,110
You girls really are fickle.

637
00:43:44,550 --> 00:43:46,030
You're such a fool.

638
00:43:47,030 --> 00:43:48,110
I don't want to talk to you anymore!

639
00:43:48,830 --> 00:43:49,630
Hey,

640
00:43:50,150 --> 00:43:51,230
what's wrong?

641
00:43:51,630 --> 00:43:53,030
The longevity noodles are ready!

642
00:43:55,790 --> 00:43:56,590
Here.

643
00:43:59,870 --> 00:44:00,590
Jianmin,

644
00:44:01,630 --> 00:44:02,710
I heard

645
00:44:03,790 --> 00:44:05,110
that even though
you caught a lot of fish,

646
00:44:05,550 --> 00:44:08,070
it was a bowl of plain noodles
that helped you win my sister's heart.

647
00:44:08,470 --> 00:44:10,110
I'm really curious.

648
00:44:10,590 --> 00:44:12,430
What kind of seasoning
did you put in the noodles?

649
00:44:13,190 --> 00:44:14,150
Were they really that good?

650
00:44:18,910 --> 00:44:23,030
Actually, it wasn't
about the taste of the noodles.

651
00:44:23,430 --> 00:44:24,190
It was...

652
00:44:26,070 --> 00:44:27,670
It was all about the timing.

653
00:44:28,990 --> 00:44:29,790
What do you mean by that?

654
00:45:40,600 --> 00:45:41,480
That day,

655
00:45:42,280 --> 00:45:43,360
a batch

656
00:45:44,200 --> 00:45:45,600
of imported medicine
arrived at our pharmacy.

657
00:45:47,920 --> 00:45:48,960
Some of the employees

658
00:45:49,880 --> 00:45:50,840
had their eyes on it.

659
00:45:50,840 --> 00:45:52,360
They stole it and tried to sell it.

660
00:45:52,840 --> 00:45:54,640
Luckily, the matter was resolved later.

661
00:45:55,280 --> 00:45:56,080
But because of that,

662
00:45:56,680 --> 00:45:58,160
I went home later than usual.

663
00:45:58,400 --> 00:45:59,680
Just as I arrived
in our apartment complex,

664
00:46:00,200 --> 00:46:01,280
the power went out.

665
00:46:01,280 --> 00:46:02,280
I knew Mao was home alone,

666
00:46:02,280 --> 00:46:03,280
so I was worried sick.

667
00:46:03,280 --> 00:46:04,600
She's so scared of the dark.

668
00:46:04,880 --> 00:46:06,480
My heart was racing,

669
00:46:06,480 --> 00:46:08,080
fearing something might happen to her.

670
00:46:40,160 --> 00:46:41,440
How did you get so badly hurt?

671
00:46:41,600 --> 00:46:43,280
Come on. Let's go to the hospital.

672
00:46:43,560 --> 00:46:44,360
I'm fine.

673
00:46:44,560 --> 00:46:45,680
I was worried about Mao,

674
00:46:45,960 --> 00:46:47,440
so I rushed home

675
00:46:47,440 --> 00:46:48,280
and stumbled.

676
00:46:48,360 --> 00:46:50,320
It's okay. I've got
all kinds of medicine here.

677
00:46:55,520 --> 00:46:57,000
With the power out
and the thunder rumbling,

678
00:46:57,720 --> 00:46:59,080
Mao was really scared.

679
00:47:00,000 --> 00:47:01,720
She tried calling you,
but you didn't pick up,

680
00:47:02,400 --> 00:47:03,800
so she found my business card.

681
00:47:21,000 --> 00:47:22,040
The plain noodles

682
00:47:23,720 --> 00:47:25,280
I ate that night

683
00:47:27,840 --> 00:47:28,760
are the best

684
00:47:29,920 --> 00:47:31,360
I've ever had in my life.

685
00:47:33,840 --> 00:47:35,960
Eat these longevity noodles
while they're hot,

686
00:47:35,960 --> 00:47:37,200
or they'll get sticky.

687
00:47:41,120 --> 00:47:41,960
Have a bite.

688
00:47:42,920 --> 00:47:43,640
No, it's...

689
00:47:43,640 --> 00:47:44,120
Just have a bite.

690
00:47:44,120 --> 00:47:45,120
It's your birthday.

691
00:47:45,200 --> 00:47:45,800
Come on.

692
00:47:53,240 --> 00:47:55,120
Whoever loses gets cake
smeared on their face, okay?

693
00:47:55,280 --> 00:47:56,400
Someone's calling from the pharmacy.

694
00:47:56,400 --> 00:47:57,760
I'll take the call.
You guys go ahead and eat.

695
00:48:01,880 --> 00:48:02,560
So who lost?

696
00:48:02,560 --> 00:48:03,560
I lost.

697
00:48:16,600 --> 00:48:17,400
Hello, Yingzi,

698
00:48:17,840 --> 00:48:19,120
we've got a new buyer,

699
00:48:19,240 --> 00:48:20,480
but the cops have been
on high alert lately.

700
00:48:20,520 --> 00:48:21,440
Should we proceed?

701
00:48:23,120 --> 00:48:25,760
Do a thorough background check
on the buyer.

702
00:48:25,760 --> 00:48:27,880
Only move forward if everything is fine.

703
00:48:29,360 --> 00:48:30,960
Be really careful
when inspecting the goods.

704
00:48:31,200 --> 00:48:33,200
Don't bring out
the real stuff right away.

705
00:48:35,640 --> 00:48:36,920
Make sure there are no slip-ups.

706
00:48:37,960 --> 00:48:40,200
Got it. I'll hang up now.

707
00:48:40,680 --> 00:48:41,240
Yingzi,

708
00:48:41,920 --> 00:48:42,880
happy birthday.

709
00:49:09,310 --> 00:49:14,630
♪Memories fade, hidden in snow♪

710
00:49:18,190 --> 00:49:23,590
♪Unclear paths, where do they go?♪

711
00:49:27,510 --> 00:49:33,830
♪Voices speak, nothing to show♪

712
00:49:36,550 --> 00:49:41,870
♪I can't hear my heart's flow♪

713
00:49:45,150 --> 00:49:53,430
♪Time chases, past and future blend♪

714
00:49:54,030 --> 00:49:59,030
♪Ambition and doubt contend♪

715
00:49:59,030 --> 00:50:03,550
♪Facing the game♪

716
00:50:04,190 --> 00:50:11,750
♪Truth hides, waiting to mend♪

717
00:50:12,350 --> 00:50:17,270
♪Who sheds their blood with such pain?♪

718
00:50:17,270 --> 00:50:24,830
♪Who writes a story
of endless ruins in vain?♪

719
00:50:40,750 --> 00:50:48,310
♪Truth hides, waiting to mend♪

720
00:50:48,910 --> 00:50:53,830
♪Whose blood and sweat♪

721
00:50:53,830 --> 00:51:01,390
"♪Is painting the vivid pictures
in this tale?♪"
